1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Personal computers
have not been very personal.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Windows 10 end-of-life just stranded
hundreds of millions of laptops.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,699
There has never been a better time
to develop new software for old hardware.

4
00:00:32,799 --> 00:00:36,000
This is AC Native.

5
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
A bare-metal creative
computing operating system.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
No desktop. No app store.
Fifty dollars per seat.

7
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:50,000
For the LACMA Art and Technology Lab,
we propose growing it into a public device library.

8
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:56,000
A lending fleet of AC Blank laptops
flashed with our OS.

9
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Circulating through Flash Days, workshops,
and Family Play afternoons at LACMA.

10
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:06,000
A public waitlist.

11
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:12,000
The library welcomes artists flashing
their own custom creative operating systems,

12
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
joining a tradition of
artist-run device libraries.

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Aesthetic Computer has been under
active development since 2021.

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Over nineteen thousand commits.
Seventeen thousand KidLisp programs.

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Twenty-eight hundred registered handles.

16
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,500
At the 2027 Symposium
we boot the cohort.

17
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,799
At the 2028 Demo Day
we play the room.

18
00:01:31,799 --> 00:01:33,299
Aesthetic.Computer.
A civic instrument.

